{
  "texts": [
    "This approach is well-suited for unlabeled data, noise-tolerant, and capable of handling complex data.",
    "Ultimately, this led to the determination of the capacitive behavior of electrode materials from thousands of scientific papers.",
    "The crux of this work lies in its use of machine learning (ML) to quickly and accurately interpret electrochemical signal images and transform them into accurate values.",
    "This is made possible by the large database of electrochemical energy storage images that is available to the ML model.",
    "This approach overcomes the limitations of human ability to interpret data, which can be too complicated in most cases (Fig. 1)."
  ]
}